main event: A US Navy supervisor spotted an unidentified object in the sky in 1959.
interesting points: The witness could not estimate the speed of the object, but estimated it was perhaps as far as a thousand yards away.
The witness was a 28-year-old male with a bachelor's degree, working as a US Navy supervisor at a plant.
The report was completed on September 2, 1959.
There are no photographs included in the report.
The report does not provide any additional details about the appearance or behavior of the unidentified object.
